---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'IMG Global in Portugal', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-compliance', text: 'D7 & D8 Visa Compliance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'portugal-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Portugal', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs Portuguese Insurers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-in-portugal', text: 'Using Your Insurance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose IMG', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Portugal', href: '/countries/portugal/insurance' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'IMG vs Cigna', href: '/compare/img-global-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'portugalPrice', header: 'Portugal (Age 35)' },
  { key: 'visaCompliant', header: 'Visa Compliant' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Global Medical Insurance', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', portugalPrice: '€70-100/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'With €2,500 Deductible', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', portugalPrice: '€50-75/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'With €5,000 Deductible', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', portugalPrice: '€40-60/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'With €10,000 Deductible', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', portugalPrice: '€30-45/mo', visaCompliant: 'Verify' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'portuguese', header: 'Portuguese Insurers' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 35)', img: '€70-100', portuguese: '€26-100' },
  { factor: 'With High Deductible', img: '€30-60', portuguese: 'Limited options' },
  { factor: 'Coverage Outside Portugal', img: 'Worldwide', portuguese: 'Limited/None' },
  { factor: 'Network in Portugal', img: 'Smaller (reimbursement)', portuguese: 'Extensive' },
  { factor: 'Annual Maximum', img: 'Up to $8M', portuguese: 'Varies' },
  { factor: 'Portability if You Move', img: 'Fully portable', portuguese: 'Must cancel' },
  { factor: 'Deductible Waiver', img: '50% outside US', portuguese: 'No' },
  { factor: 'AIMA Accepted', img: 'Generally yes', portuguese: 'Yes' },
];

const savingsColumns = [
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage Type' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'premium', header: 'Premium Insurers' },
  { key: 'savings', header: 'Annual Savings' },
];

const savingsRows = [
  { coverage: 'Low deductible', img: '€840-1,200/yr', premium: '€1,560-2,040/yr', savings: '€720-840' },
  { coverage: '€2,500 deductible', img: '€600-900/yr', premium: '€1,200-1,680/yr', savings: '€600-780' },
  { coverage: '€5,000 deductible', img: '€480-720/yr', premium: 'Limited options', savings: '€500+' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="IMG Global Health Insurance in Portugal"
  description="Complete guide to using IMG Global in Portugal. Budget-friendly international coverage for D7 and D8 visa holders with high-deductible savings."
  headline="IMG Global Health Insurance in Portugal"
  subheadline="Budget-friendly international coverage for expats in Portugal. High-deductible strategy, visa compliance, and real cost comparisons."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/portugal-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an IMG Portugal Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/img-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">IMG Global in Portugal</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global offers a budget-friendly path to international health insurance for expats in Portugal. While not as well-known as Cigna or BUPA, IMG provides solid coverage at lower price points, making it attractive for cost-conscious D7 and D8 visa holders.
  </p>
  <p>
    The key value proposition: IMG's high-deductible options and 50% deductible waiver for treatment outside the US make it one of the most affordable international insurance options for Portugal-based expats.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$8M</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Max annual limit</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">50%</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Deductible waiver outside US</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">30+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Years in business</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Portugal-Specific Quote"
    description="See what IMG Global costs for expats living in Portugal."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/img-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-compliance">D7 & D8 Visa Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global is generally accepted for Portuguese visa applications, though it's less commonly used than Cigna or Allianz. Verify acceptance with your specific consulate.
  </p>

  <h3>Stage 1: Consulate Application</h3>
  <p>
    For D7 (passive income) or D8 (digital nomad) visa applications:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Minimum €30,000 coverage (IMG Global Medical Insurance exceeds this)</li>
    <li>Valid in Portugal/Schengen Area</li>
    <li>At least 1 year duration</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    IMG's Global Medical Insurance meets Schengen requirements with coverage up to $8M annual maximum.
  </p>

  <h3>Stage 2: AIMA Residency</h3>
  <p>
    For AIMA appointments, travel insurance is rejected. IMG Global Medical Insurance qualifies because it's:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Long-term health insurance (not travel insurance)</li>
    <li>12-month renewable terms</li>
    <li>Comprehensive inpatient and outpatient coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-900 mb-2">Verify First</h3>
    <p class="text-yellow-800">
      IMG is less commonly used for Portuguese visas than Cigna or Allianz. While their Global Medical Insurance should meet requirements, confirm acceptance with your specific consulate before purchasing. Request documentation showing IMG meets Schengen health insurance requirements.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="portugal-network">Network Coverage in Portugal</h2>
  <p>
    IMG has a smaller network in Portugal compared to premium competitors. Most expats use the reimbursement model: pay providers directly, then submit claims for reimbursement.
  </p>

  <h3>How It Works in Practice</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Any licensed provider:</strong> See any doctor or hospital in Portugal</li>
    <li><strong>Pay at time of service:</strong> Pay the provider with your card or cash</li>
    <li><strong>Submit for reimbursement:</strong> Upload receipt via IMG app or portal</li>
    <li><strong>Fast processing:</strong> Typical reimbursement in 5-10 business days</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    This works well in Portugal because:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Healthcare costs are affordable (GP €30-50, specialist €60-100)</li>
    <li>Portuguese providers issue detailed receipts (facturas)</li>
    <li>You have complete freedom of provider choice</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Emergency Care</h3>
  <p>
    For emergencies, go to the nearest hospital. IMG covers emergency care at any facility. Contact IMG's 24/7 assistance line for help with hospital admission or if you need medical evacuation.
  </p>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global offers Global Medical Insurance with flexible deductible options:
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices for worldwide coverage excluding USA. Lower prices than many competitors due to IMG's focus on value.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>The 50% Deductible Waiver</h3>
  <p>
    IMG's standout feature: if you choose a deductible and receive treatment outside the US, your deductible is reduced by 50%. In Portugal:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>€5,000 deductible becomes €2,500 effective deductible</li>
    <li>€2,500 deductible becomes €1,250 effective deductible</li>
    <li>Combined with affordable Portuguese healthcare, this makes high-deductible plans very practical</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Savings Comparison</h3>
  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={savingsColumns} rows={savingsRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Coverage Highlights</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Annual maximum:</strong> Up to $8M</li>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital, surgery, ICU fully covered</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, labs, imaging</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency evacuation:</strong> Up to $500K</li>
    <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Available after waiting period</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Included (verify limits)</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Calculate Your Savings"
    description="See how much you can save with IMG's high-deductible options."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/img-global"
  />

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs Portuguese Insurers</h2>
  <p>
    How does IMG Global compare to Portuguese insurance companies?
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Choose IMG Global If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Budget is a major consideration</li>
    <li>You're comfortable with reimbursement model</li>
    <li>High-deductible strategy appeals to you</li>
    <li>You travel outside Portugal and want worldwide coverage</li>
    <li>You might relocate from Portugal</li>
    <li>Maximum coverage limits matter (up to $8M)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Choose a Portuguese Insurer If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You want direct billing at local hospitals</li>
    <li>Extensive local network is important</li>
    <li>You prefer Portuguese-language processes</li>
    <li>You're staying in Portugal permanently</li>
    <li>You plan to transition to SNS</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Choose a Premium International Insurer If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You want larger Portuguese networks</li>
    <li>Direct billing is important to you</li>
    <li>You have significant pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Mental health parity is essential</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <a href="/countries/portugal/insurance">See all Portugal insurance options →</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="claims-in-portugal">Using Your Insurance in Portugal</h2>

  <h3>Reimbursement Process</h3>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
    <li>See any licensed provider in Portugal</li>
    <li>Pay at time of service (get detailed factura)</li>
    <li>Submit claim via IMG app or online portal</li>
    <li>Processing typically 5-10 business days</li>
    <li>Reimbursement to your bank account</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Documentation Tips</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Portuguese facturas are accepted without translation</li>
    <li>Keep itemized receipts (not just credit card receipts)</li>
    <li>Include diagnosis codes when available</li>
    <li>Submit promptly (within 90 days)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>IMG MyIMG App</h3>
  <p>
    The IMG app lets you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Submit claims with photo upload</li>
    <li>Track claim status</li>
    <li>Access your digital ID card</li>
    <li>Contact 24/7 assistance</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>24/7 Support</h3>
  <p>
    IMG offers round-the-clock assistance for emergencies, hospital coordination, and general support. Available in English with translation services.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose IMG in Portugal</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Budget-conscious D7/D8 visa holders</li>
        <li>Healthy individuals comfortable with higher deductibles</li>
        <li>Expats who prefer provider freedom</li>
        <li>Digital nomads who travel frequently</li>
        <li>Those who want maximum coverage limits</li>
        <li>Expats comfortable with reimbursement</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Those who want direct billing</li>
        <li>Expats with significant pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Those who prefer established name brands</li>
        <li>People who want local Portuguese insurers</li>
        <li>Those needing extensive mental health coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is IMG Global accepted at AIMA?</h3>
  <p>
    Generally yes, as IMG Global Medical Insurance is long-term health insurance (not travel insurance) with comprehensive coverage. However, confirm with your consulate before purchasing, as IMG is less commonly used for Portuguese visas than larger insurers.
  </p>

  <h3>How does the 50% deductible waiver work?</h3>
  <p>
    When you receive treatment outside the US, your deductible is automatically reduced by 50%. If you chose a $5,000 deductible, you only need to meet $2,500 in Portugal before coverage kicks in. This happens automatically — no need to request it.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use IMG Global with SNS?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. Once you have your SNS number (Número de Utente), you can use public healthcare for routine care and keep IMG for emergencies, private care, or coverage outside Portugal.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I need hospitalization?</h3>
  <p>
    Go to any hospital. Contact IMG's assistance line — they can help coordinate with the hospital, arrange direct payment for large expenses, and provide support throughout your stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Does IMG cover pre-existing conditions?</h3>
  <p>
    IMG typically excludes pre-existing conditions or applies waiting periods. If you have significant health conditions, consider BUPA Global or Cigna which may offer more favorable handling.
  </p>

  <h3>How does IMG compare to SafetyWing?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is travel insurance for nomads; IMG Global Medical Insurance is comprehensive international health insurance. SafetyWing won't be accepted at AIMA for residency. IMG is actual health insurance that meets visa requirements.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Budget-Friendly Coverage?"
    description="Get a personalized IMG Global quote for your situation in Portugal."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/img-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Visa acceptance, pricing, and coverage terms change. We are not insurance brokers or immigration consultants. Verify all information with IMG Global, AIMA, and your consulate before making decisions.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
